---

Slice the @Sugar Snap Peas{80} in half lengthways.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{2} to the water and bring back to the
boil. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

> Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240} and fry until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and
discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The beef
> is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the beef has browned, add the sugar snaps, @Red Thai Style Paste{50} and
garlic to the pan.

Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the cooked noodles, @Ketjap Manis{50}, @Water for the Sauce{100} and
@Sugar for the Sauce{1/2} to the pan. Stir to combine and piping hot, then
remove from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When ready, share the beef noodles between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5} to finish.

Enjoy!